level.heading: Prior Codifications
level.text: Temporary Repeal of Section Section 17 of D.C. Law 17-63 repealed this section as of the date when the District of Columbia Free Clinic Captive Insurance Company becomes operational.
Section 19(b) of D.C. Law 17-63 provided that the act shall expire after 225 days of its having taken effect.

level.heading: Editor’s Notes
level.text: Repeal of Part B: Section 16 of D.C. Law 17-196 provided: "The Free Clinic Assistance Program Act of 1986, effective September 23, 1986 (D.C. Law 6-155; D.C. Official Code § 1-307.21 et seq.), is repealed as of the date when the Agency becomes operational."
